[assistant] {"action":"advisory_preparation","summary":"Vert.x Web Client 5.0.1 uses Vert.x/Netty 4.2.x and meaningful tests can run against an in-process HTTP server, but Java 25 native runs need the same Netty unsafe-access runtime properties already used for 5.0.0.","deterministic_setup":[],"agent_guidance":"Set native test runtime system properties for 5.0.1: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Meaningful coverage should use Vertx.vertx(), WebClient/WebClientSession/CachingWebClient, and a local 127.0.0.1 Vert.x HttpServer; no external service is normally required. Avoid OAuth2WebClient coverage unless intentionally adding the optional OAuth dependency.","risks":["The failing native-image run remains authoritative; these properties address the documented Netty 4.2 Java 24+/25 unsafe default but local verification may reveal additional metadata needs.","OAuth2-specific APIs reference the optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 dependency; base WebClient coverage does not require it."]}
